Add delete permission for agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes\n445:   - [ ] Add delete permission for extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxclaims\n446:   - [ ] Add list permission for pods (for verification)\n447: - [ ] Update ClusterRole or Role in deployment manifests\n448: - [ ] Verify WorkloadManager service account has correct permissions\n449: - [ ] Implement authorization checks in handler (optional)\n450:   - [ ] Verify user has permission to delete in sandbox's namespace\n451:   - [ ] Use Kubernetes SubjectAccessReview API\n452: - [ ] Create security tests\n453:   - [ ] Test deletion with insufficient permissions\n454:   - [ ] Test deletion with proper permissions\n455:   - [ ] Test cross-namespace deletion (should fail)\n456: \n457: **Verification**: Run security tests to verify RBAC permissions are correct\n458: \n459: ---\n460: \n461: ### Task 19: Create comprehensive documentation\n462: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/README.md` (if not exists or update)\n463:   - [ ] Overview of WorkloadManager package\n464:   - [ ] Architecture diagram\n465:   - [ ] GarbageCollector documentation\n466:   - [ ] Sandbox lifecycle documentation\n467: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/README.md`\n468:   - [ ] SandboxController documentation\n469:   - [ ] DeleteSession API documentation\n470:   - [ ] Usage examples\n471: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/README.md`\n472:   - [ ] HTTP handler documentation\n473:   - [ ] DELETE endpoint documentation\n474:   - [ ] Request/response examples\n475: - [ Create `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.md` (or include in main README)\n476:   - [ ] GarbageCollector design overview\n477:   - [ ] Configuration options\n478:   - [ ] Cleanup strategies\n479: - [ ] Update API documentation\n480:   - [ ] Document DELETE /v1/sessions/:sessionId endpoint\n481:   - [ ] Include request/response examples\n482:   - [ ] Document error codes\n483: - [ ] Update configuration documentation\n484:   - [ ] Document GCInterval configuration\n485:   - [ ] Document timeout configurations\n486:   - [ ] Document label and annotation constants\n487: \n488: **Verification**: Review documentation for completeness and accuracy\n489: \n490: ---\n491: \n492: ### Task 20: Final verification and cleanup\n493: - [ ] Run full test suite: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n494:   - [ ] Verify all unit tests pass\n495:   - [ ] Verify all integration tests pass\n496: - [ ] Run static analysis: `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n497:   - [ ] Fix any warnings or errors\n498: - [ ] Run linter if configured (e.g., golangci-lint)\n499:   - [ ] Fix any linting issues\n500: - [ ] Run gofmt: `gofmt -s -w ./pkg/workloadmanager/`\n501:   - [ ] Ensure code is properly formatted\n502: - [ ] Update go.mod: `go mod tidy`\n503:   - [ ] Remove unused dependencies\n504:   - [ ] Update go.sum\n505: - [ ] Build package: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n506:   - [ ] Verify all packages build successfully\n507: - [ ] Test end-to-end workflow\n508:   - [ ] Create sandbox via AR-005\n509:   - [ ] Wait for expiration\n510:   - [ ] Verify GarbageCollector cleans up\n511:   - [ ] Test manual deletion\n512:   - [ ] Verify resources are properly cleaned\n513: - [ ] Create CHANGELOG entry for AR-006\n514: - [ ] Update main project README with AR-006 information\n515: - [ ] Tag release if applicable\n516: \n517: **Verification**: All tests pass, code is linted, packages build successfully, end-to-end workflow works\n518: \n519: ---\n520: \n521: ## Summary\n522: \n523: **Total Tasks**: 20\n524: **Estimated Effort**: M (Medium) - 10-15 hours\n525: \n526: ### Key Deliverables\n527: 1. **GarbageCollector** - Automatic cleanup of idle and expired sandboxes\n528: 2. **SandboxController.DeleteSession** - Manual deletion API\n529: 3. **HTTP Handler** - DELETE /v1/sessions/:sessionId endpoint\n530: 4. **Store Extensions** - ListInactiveSandboxes, ListExpiredSandboxes methods\n531: 5. **K8sClient Deletion** - DeleteSandbox method\n532: 6. **API Types** -