xes are deleted\n  - [ ] Verify active sandboxes are preserved\n- [ ] Test GC with different configurations\n  - [ ] Test with DryRun enabled\n  - [ ] Test with namespace filters\n  - [ ] Test with label selectors\n  - [ ] Test with different thresholds\n- [ ] Test GC error scenarios\n  - [ ] Test with store offline\n  - [ ] Test with K8s API unavailable\n  - [ ] Verify graceful degradation\n- [ ] Test metrics and logging\n  - [ ] Verify metrics are updated\n  - [ ] Verify logs are emitted\n  - [ ] Verify events are recorded\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/gc -run TestIntegration` to verify integration tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 18: Final verification and cleanup\n- [ ] Run full test suite: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n  - [ ] Verify all unit tests pass\n  - [ ] Verify all integration tests pass\n- [ ] Run static analysis: `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n  - [ ] Fix any warnings or errors\n- [ ] Run linter if configured (e.g., golangci-lint)\n  - [ ] Fix any linting issues\n- [ ] Run gofmt: `gofmt -s -w ./pkg/workloadmanager/`\n  - [ ] Ensure code is properly formatted\n- [ ] Update go.mod: `go mod tidy`\n  - [ ] Remove unused dependencies\n  - [ ] Update go.sum\n- [ ] Build package: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n  - [ ] Verify all packages build successfully\n- [ ] Test end-to-end workflow\n  - [ ] Start WorkloadManager server with GC enabled\n  - [ ] Create sandbox sessions\n  - [ ] Wait for GC cycles\n  - [ ] Verify cleanup occurs\n  - [ ] Verify metrics are collected\n  - [ ] Verify logs are emitted\n- [ ] Create CHANGELOG entry for AR-008\n- [ ] Update main project README with AR-008 information\n- [ ] Tag release if applicable\n\n**Verification**: All tests pass, code is linted, packages build successfully, end-to-end workflow works\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Total Tasks**: 18\n**Estimated Effort**: S (Small) - 8-12 hours\n\n### Key Deliverables\n1. **GC Package** - `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/` with scheduler, collector, policy, and metrics\n2. **GCScheduler** - Scheduled GC execution with configurable intervals\n3. **GCCollector** - GC collection logic with candidate identification and deletion\n4. **GCPolicy** - Configurable GC policies for expired, idle, and orphaned sandboxes\n5. **GCMetrics** - Prometheus metrics for GC operations\n6. **Configuration** - GC configuration support in WorkloadManager\n7. **Integration** - GC scheduler integrated into WorkloadManager server\n8. **Tests** - Comprehensive unit and integration tests\n9. **Documentation** - Complete documentation for GC functionality\n10. **RBAC Updates** - Permissions for GC operations\n\n### Success Criteria\n- All unit tests pass with >80% code coverage\n- All integration tests pass\n- GC scheduler runs periodically\n- Expired sandboxes are identified and deleted\n- Idle sandboxes are identified and deleted\n- Orphaned sandboxes are identified and deleted\n- Resources are properly cleaned up (K8s + Store)\n- DryRun mode works correctly\n- Metrics are emitted correctly\n- Events are recorded correctly\n- Logs are structured and informative\n- RBAC permissions are correct\n- Code passes static analysis and linting\n- Documentation is complete and accurate\n\n### Dependencies\n- Go 1.24+\n- Kubernetes cluster (for testing)\n- Redis/Valkey (for session store)\n- agent-sandbox CRD (agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1)\n- SandboxClaim CRD (extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1)\n- AR-006 (Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management) - for basic GC functionality\n- k8s.io/client-go v0.34.1\n- k8s.io/api v0.34.1\n- k8s.io/apimachinery v0.34.1\n- go-redis/v9 or valkey-go (Redis client)\n- prometheus/client_golang (metrics)\n- sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime (event recorder)\n\n### Blocked By\n- None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n\n### Blocks\n- None (this is an enhancement to AR-006, can proceed independently)\n\n### Notes\n- AR-008 enhances the basic GC functionality from AR-006 with:\n  - More sophisticated scheduling\n  - Configurable policies\n  - Metrics and observability\n  - Event recording\n  - Better configuration options\n- GC runs independently in background, can be started/stopped with server\n- DryRun mode allows testing without actual deletions\n- Namespace and label filtering allows selective GC\n- Idempotency ensures safe retries and concurrent operations\n- Error handling is designed to be resilient to transient failures\n- Metrics provide visibility into GC operations for monitoring and alerting","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/controller.go\">\nERROR [57:3] unknown field MetricsBindAddress in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [58:3] unknown field Port in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [62:3] unknown field SyncPeriod in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [88:17] undefined: AgentRuntimeReconciler\nERROR [98:15] cannot use ctrl.Options{…} (value of struct type controllerruntime.Options) as \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/controller\".TypedOptions[reconcile.Request] value in argument to ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).WithEventFilter(&ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate{}).WithOptions\nERROR [98:28] unknown field MaxConcurrentReconciles in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [118:15] cannot use ctrl.Options{…} (value of struct type controllerruntime.Options) as \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/controller\".TypedOptions[reconcile.Request] value in argument to ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).For(&runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{}).WithEventFilter(&ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate{}).WithOptions\nERROR [118:28] unknown field 